## BP-001: System model definition

test TC-SYS-001 "Parse valid system model"
  verifies: BP-001
  given: a sys/ directory containing valid .req, .iface,
         .component, and .testspec files
  expect: a structured SystemModel with all elements populated
          and no errors

test TC-SYS-002 "Reject non-text model files"
  verifies: BP-001
  given: a sys/ directory containing a binary file with a
         .req extension
  expect: a syntax error reported with file path and description

test TC-SYS-003 "Handle empty model directory"
  verifies: BP-001
  given: a sys/ directory with no model files
  expect: a valid but empty SystemModel with no errors

## BP-002: Model validation

test TC-SYS-004 "Valid model passes validation"
  verifies: BP-002
  given: a SystemModel where all cross-references resolve
  expect: ValidationResult{valid: true, errors: []}

test TC-SYS-005 "Broken satisfies reference detected"
  verifies: BP-002
  given: a component with satisfies: REQ-NONEXISTENT
  expect: ValidationResult{valid: false} with an error
         referencing the broken link

test TC-SYS-006 "Broken verifies reference detected"
  verifies: BP-002
  given: a test spec with verifies: REQ-NONEXISTENT
  expect: ValidationResult{valid: false} with an error
         referencing the broken link

test TC-SYS-007 "Broken depends_on reference detected"
  verifies: BP-002
  given: a component with depends_on: COMP-NONEXISTENT
  expect: ValidationResult{valid: false} with an error
         referencing the broken link

## BP-003: Validation error reporting

test TC-SYS-008 "Errors include file and line number"
  verifies: BP-003
  given: a SystemModel with a broken reference on line 5
         of components/parser/parser.component
  expect: ValidationError with source_file containing
         "parser.component" and line_number: 5

test TC-SYS-009 "Non-zero exit on validation failure"
  verifies: BP-003
  given: a SystemModel with at least one validation error
  when: validation is invoked
  expect: process exits with non-zero status

test TC-SYS-010 "Zero exit on validation success"
  verifies: BP-003
  given: a SystemModel with no validation errors
  when: validation is invoked
  expect: process exits with zero status

## BP-004: Agent context generation

test TC-SYS-011 "Assemble context for a single component"
  verifies: BP-004
  given: a valid SystemModel with one component COMP-001
         that satisfies REQ-001, consumes InterfaceA,
         and is verified by TC-001
  when: context assembly is requested for COMP-001
  expect: AgentContext containing the component definition,
         REQ-001, InterfaceA, and TC-001

test TC-SYS-012 "Context includes parent system requirements"
  verifies: BP-004
  given: a component with derived requirement BP-001-P01
         (derived_from: BP-001)
  when: context is assembled for that component
  expect: AgentContext includes both BP-001-P01 and BP-001

test TC-SYS-013 "Context resolves interface references"
  verifies: BP-004
  given: a component that consumes InterfaceA, which
         references InterfaceB in a field type
  when: context is assembled for that component
  expect: AgentContext includes both InterfaceA and InterfaceB

## BP-005: Traceability

test TC-SYS-014 "Forward trace from requirement"
  verifies: BP-005
  given: REQ-001 satisfied by COMP-001, verified by TC-001
  when: forward trace is requested for REQ-001
  expect: TraceResult showing COMP-001 in satisfied_by
         and TC-001 in verified_by

test TC-SYS-015 "Backward trace from test spec"
  verifies: BP-005
  given: TC-001 verifies REQ-001
  when: backward trace is requested for TC-001
  expect: TraceResult showing REQ-001 as the traced requirement

test TC-SYS-016 "Trace follows derived_from chain"
  verifies: BP-005
  given: BP-001-P01 derived_from BP-001
  when: backward trace is requested for BP-001-P01
  expect: TraceResult includes BP-001 as the root
         system requirement

test TC-SYS-017 "Full traceability matrix"
  verifies: BP-005
  given: a valid SystemModel with requirements, components,
         and test specs
  when: full traceability matrix is requested
  expect: every requirement appears with its satisfying
         components and verifying test specs

## BP-006: Coverage analysis

test TC-SYS-018 "Detect uncovered requirement"
  verifies: BP-006
  given: REQ-001 has no test spec with verifies: REQ-001
  when: coverage analysis is requested
  expect: CoverageReport with REQ-001 in uncovered_requirements

test TC-SYS-019 "Detect unallocated requirement"
  verifies: BP-006
  given: REQ-001 has no component with satisfies: REQ-001
  when: coverage analysis is requested
  expect: CoverageReport with REQ-001 in uncovered_requirements

test TC-SYS-020 "Full coverage reports 100%"
  verifies: BP-006
  given: every requirement is verified by at least one test spec
  when: coverage analysis is requested
  expect: CoverageReport{coverage_percentage: 100.0,
         uncovered_requirements: []}

test TC-SYS-021 "Coverage metrics are accurate"
  verifies: BP-006
  given: 4 requirements, 3 covered by test specs, 1 uncovered
  when: coverage analysis is requested
  expect: CoverageReport{total_requirements: 4,
         covered_requirements: 3, coverage_percentage: 75.0}

## BP-007: Change detection

test TC-SYS-022 "Detect added model element"
  verifies: BP-007
  given: a new .req file added since the last sync
  expect: ChangeSet includes the new requirement as
         change_type: added

test TC-SYS-023 "Detect modified model element"
  verifies: BP-007
  given: an existing .component file modified since the last sync
  expect: ChangeSet includes the component as
         change_type: modified

test TC-SYS-024 "Detect removed model element"
  verifies: BP-007
  given: a .req file removed since the last sync
  expect: ChangeSet includes the requirement as
         change_type: removed

test TC-SYS-025 "Transitive impact detection"
  verifies: BP-007
  given: InterfaceA is modified, COMP-001 consumes InterfaceA,
         COMP-002 depends_on COMP-001
  expect: ChangeSet affected_components includes both
         COMP-001 and COMP-002

## BP-008: Incremental sync

test TC-SYS-026 "Sync regenerates only affected components"
  verifies: BP-008
  given: COMP-001 is in the ChangeSet, COMP-003 is not
  when: sync is requested
  expect: context is assembled for COMP-001 only,
         COMP-003 is untouched

test TC-SYS-027 "Sync with no changes is a no-op"
  verifies: BP-008
  given: no model files changed since the last sync
  when: sync is requested
  expect: ChangeSet{affected_components: [], changes: []}
         and no context is assembled

## BP-009: Visual model representation

test TC-SYS-028 "Visual output includes all components"
  verifies: BP-009
  given: a SystemModel with 3 components
  when: visual representation is requested
  expect: output contains all 3 components with their names

test TC-SYS-029 "Visual output shows dependencies"
  verifies: BP-009
  given: COMP-002 depends_on COMP-001
  when: visual representation is requested
  expect: output shows a dependency link from COMP-002
         to COMP-001

test TC-SYS-030 "Visual output shows traceability"
  verifies: BP-009
  given: COMP-001 satisfies REQ-001, TC-001 verifies REQ-001
  when: visual representation is requested
  expect: output shows satisfy and verify links
